Title: The Dynamics of Institutional and Individual Trading 
Abstract:
 We study the daily and intradaily cross-sectional relation between stock
 returns and the trading of institutional and individual investors in
 Nasdaq 100 securities. Based on the previous day's stock return, the top
 performing decile of securities is 23.9% more likely to be bought in net
 by institutions (and sold by individuals) than those in the bottom
 performance decile. Strong contemporaneous daily patterns can largely be
 explained by net institutional (individual) trading positively
 (negatively) following past intradaily excess stock returns (or the news
 associated therein). In comparison, evidence of return predictability and
 price pressure are economically small. Copyright 2003 by the American Finance Association. 
