Author-Name: Liuren Wu 
Author-Workplace-Name: Zicklin School of Business, Baruch College, CUNY 
Title: What Type of Process Underlies Options? A Simple Robust Test 
Abstract:
 We develop a simple robust method to distinguish the presence of
 continuous and discontinuous components in the price of an asset
 underlying options. Our method examines the prices of at-the-money and
 out-of-the-money options as the option's time-to-maturity approaches zero.
 We show that these prices converge to zero at speeds that depend upon
 whether the underlying asset price process is purely continuous, purely
 discontinuous, or a combination of both. We apply the method to S&P 500
 index options and find the existence of both a continuous component and a
 jump component in the index. Copyright 2003 by the American Finance Association. 
