Title: Do Price Discreteness and Transactions Costs Affect Stock Returns? Comparing Ex-Dividend Pricing before and after Decimalization 
Abstract:
 By the end of January 2001, all NYSE stocks had converted their price
 quotations from 1/8s and 1/16s to decimals. This study examines the effect
 of this change in price quotations on ex-dividend day activity. We find
 that abnormal ex-dividend day returns increase in the 1/16 and decimal
 pricing eras, relative to the 1/8 era, which is inconsistent with
 microstructure explanations of ex-day price movements. We also find that
 abnormal returns increase in conjunction with a May 1997 reduction in the
 capital gains tax rate, as they should if relative taxation of dividends
 and capital gains affects ex-day pricing. Copyright 2003 by the American Finance Association. 
